Latitude and longitude are numbers used to describe the position of a place on Earth. Latitude shows how far a place is north or south of the Equator. It ranges from -90 to 90. Positive values mean the place is in the northern part of the Earth, while negative values mean it is in the southern part.

Longitude shows how far a place is east or west of the Prime Meridian. It ranges from -180 to 180. Positive values mean the place is to the east, while negative values mean it is to the west.

These coordinates help us locate any place on Earth accurately. In this program, latitude and longitude are used as input values to calculate the distance between two points.